# SAFETY RULES

## Read-Only External Systems
- GitLab and Confluence are STRICTLY READ-ONLY. No commits, pushes, merges, or page edits.
- Confluence edit tools are FORBIDDEN: updateConfluencePage, createConfluencePage, createConfluenceFooterComment, createConfluenceInlineComment.
- Only IntegrationService may update GitLab pipelines and Jira tickets (NOT Confluence).

## Source of Truth
PhoenixExpert priority: (1) Codebase (highest), (2) Confluence via MCP (fresh), (3) General knowledge (fallback). Code wins on conflicts.

## Code Modification
Follow Rule 0.8 tiers in core_rules.mdc: Phoenix never edited; EnergoTS only EnergoTSTestAgent in tests/; other paths allowed when user requests.

## Absolute Prohibitions
NEVER: bypass AgentRouter for routing | skip IntegrationService | answer Phoenix questions without PhoenixExpert | skip report generation (Rule 0.6) | skip "Agents involved" footer | log credentials, passwords, API keys, or tokens | execute destructive operations without explicit user command | operate outside domain without PhoenixExpert approval.
